Playwright MCP Local Setup Guide (Clean Steps)

1. Install Node.js (LTS v20) from https://nodejs.org and verify using: node -v, npm -v

2. Install Git from https://git-scm.com and verify using: git --version

3. Create project folder: mkdir Test and open it

4. Clone repository: git clone https://github.com/microsoft/playwright-mcp.git

5. Go inside folder: cd playwright-mcp

6. Install dependencies: npm install

7. Run MCP server: node cli.js

8. Create folder: Test/.vscode

9. Create file: mcp.json inside .vscode

10. Add config:

{
 "servers": {
   "playwright-local": {
     "command": "node",
     "args": [
       "FULL_PATH\Test\playwright-mcp\cli.js"
     ]
   }
 }
}

11. Open VS Code with 'Test' folder (not playwright-mcp)

12. Restart VS Code

13. Open Chat panel → Configure Tools → Enable 'playwright-local'

14. Test with prompt: Use playwright tool to open https://google.com and take screenshot
